                {"src": "calvin", "attr": "Calvin's Commentaries", "html": "<p>He means to intimate that there had been a time when sin was dead to him or in him. But he is not to be understood as though he had been without law at any time; this word has a peculiar import — there was a time when the law's demands had not yet penetrated his full consciousness, and in that time he had a kind of life.</p>"},
