                {"src": "wesley", "attr": "John Wesley's Notes", "html": "<p>The commandment — that is, every branch of the law. Is holy, and just, and good — it springs from, and partakes of, the holy nature of God; it is every way just and right in itself; it is designed wholly for the good of man. The fault that produced death lay entirely in sin, not in the law.</p>"},
